  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: 0f3a2c8c7b8f4d9c9d5a3d11d5f50101, type: 3}
  m_Name: PokedexGoldfinch
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: 
  entryId: bird_goldfinch
  commonName: American Goldfinch
  scientificName: Spinus tristi
  icon: {fileID: 2800000, guid: da3c3b0529a80f741a1e99f05d689d0a, type: 3}
  category: Bird
  habitat: Fields & Forest Edges
  height: 11 - 14 cm
  weight: 11 - 20 g
  diet: Granivore
  rarity: Common
  shortDescription: A small, lively finch that displays a bright, canary-yellow body
    during the breeding season.
  behaviorNotes: Flies in a distinctive, bouncy, undulating pattern. Moves in social,
    chattering flocks.
  observationTips: Look for them clinging to thistles or sunflowers. They rarely
    spend time on dense forest floors.
  funFact: They are among the strictest vegetarians in the bird world, eating seeds
    almost exclusively and even feeding their young a seed-based diet.
  facts:
  - They are among the latest-nesting birds in North America, waiting until July
    or August when thistle and milkweed plants seed.
  - Their nesting material is woven so tightly with plant down and spider silk that
    the finished cup can actually hold water.
  - Goldfinches undergo a complete plumage molt twice a year, changing from dull
    olive brown in winter to bright yellow in summer.
